<paragraph id="D611747CE85DA5785C8E55FBFE09A1A3" blockId="14.[151,741,151,214]" box="[151,487,187,214]" pageId="14" pageNumber="51">(2021-FLP-IMM-0352, 0555)</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="9EB427F7E85DA5785C8E5443FD1AA3B8" pageId="14" pageNumber="51" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph id="D611747CE85DA5785C8E5443FE15A0A4" blockId="14.[151,1437,259,717]" pageId="14" pageNumber="51">
<emphasis id="E4DAA86EE85DA5785C8E5443FEC9A068" bold="true" box="[151,295,259,285]" pageId="14" pageNumber="51">Host plants.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="11AE0FFFE85DA5785D375443FE21A068" box="[302,463,259,285]" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Olyra" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="14" pageNumber="51" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="latifolia">
<emphasis id="E4DAA86EE85DA5785D375443FE21A068" box="[302,463,259,285]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="51">Olyra latifolia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
L. (
<taxonomicName id="11AE0FFFE85DA5785DE45443FDB1A068" authorityName="Barnhart" authorityYear="1895" baseAuthorityName="R.Br." box="[509,607,259,285]" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="14" pageNumber="51" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Poaceae</taxonomicName>
: 
<taxonomicName id="11AE0FFFE85DA5785E735443FCFDA068" authorityName="Luerssen" authorityYear="1893" box="[618,787,259,285]" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="14" pageNumber="51" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Bambusoideae">Bambusoideae</taxonomicName>
: 
<taxonomicName id="11AE0FFFE85DA5785F075443FC96A06B" box="[798,888,259,286]" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="14" pageNumber="51" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="tribe" tribe="Olyreae">Olyreae</taxonomicName>
) (
<figureCitation id="4E9568F9E85DA5785F965443FC3BA068" box="[911,981,259,285]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="13.[151,250,1878,1902]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,194,1843]" captionTargetId="figure-17@13.[151,1436,181,1855]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURE 6. Host plants for Magneuptychia harpyia: Olyra latifolia L.: 1a) leaves; 1b) close-up view of the nodes; 1c) close-up view of inflorescence materials; 1d) host plant in situ. 1e) Taquara micrantha in situ 2a, b) adult of Magneuptychia harpyia in dorsal and ventral view (based on 2021-FLP-IMM-0352)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6420378" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6420378/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="51">Fig. 6</figureCitation>
: 1a–d). Based on 2021-FLP-IMM-0352, the larva was found on a plant in a primary forest located on a property adjacent to FLP (Monterrey). This plant species is typically found in areas of limited light availability and usually grows in groups of a few individuals, near other species of herbaceous plants of similar size. The collection was made when the plant was 
<quantity id="1156D999E85DA57858A5542FFB15A0FF" box="[1212,1275,367,394]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.0" pageId="14" pageNumber="51" unit="m" value="0.8">0.8 m</quantity>
tall. The larva was found at a distance of 
<quantity id="1156D999E85DA5785DD154D3FDE7A0DB" box="[456,521,403,430]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.0" pageId="14" pageNumber="51" unit="m" value="0.8">0.8 m</quantity>
from the ground, on the abaxial leaf surface, at the base of the leaf blade, just at the margin of the leaf (
<tableCitation id="9B2C41C7E85DA5785D8F54F7FE00A0A4" box="[406,494,439,465]" captionStart="TABLE 2" captionStartId="5.[151,239,517,543]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="TABLE 2. Details of sampled materials with information on the host plant conditions. Abbreviations: abaxial (AB); adaxial (AD); distal (D); middle (M); proximal (P); midrib (B); middle (E); margin (IN); new (N); mature (MA); old (O); none (NO); light (L); mid (MI); heavy (H)." pageId="14" pageNumber="51">Table 2</tableCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="D611747CE85DA5785CDE549CFF2CA36C" blockId="14.[151,1437,259,717]" pageId="14" pageNumber="51">
<taxonomicName id="11AE0FFFE85DA5785CDE549CFCBFA080" authority="(Kunth) I. L. C. Oliveira &amp; R. P. Oliveira" authorityName="I. L. C. Oliveira &amp; R. P. Oliveira" baseAuthorityName="Kunth" box="[199,849,475,502]" class="Arachnida" family="Cryptogeobiidae" genus="Taquara" kingdom="Animalia" order="Opiliones" pageId="14" pageNumber="51" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="micrantha">
<emphasis id="E4DAA86EE85DA5785CDE549CFE71A080" box="[199,415,475,501]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="51">Taquara micrantha</emphasis>
(Kunth) I.L.C.Oliveira &amp; R.P.Oliveira
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName id="11AE0FFFE85DA5785F79549BFC2CA080" authorityName="Barnhart" authorityYear="1895" baseAuthorityName="R.Br." box="[864,962,475,501]" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="14" pageNumber="51" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Poaceae</taxonomicName>
: 
<taxonomicName id="11AE0FFFE85DA5785FD4549BFB98A080" authorityName="Luerssen" authorityYear="1893" box="[973,1142,475,501]" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="14" pageNumber="51" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Bambusoideae">Bambusoideae</taxonomicName>
: 
<taxonomicName id="11AE0FFFE85DA5785899549BFB34A083" box="[1152,1242,475,502]" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="14" pageNumber="51" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="tribe" tribe="Olyreae">Olyreae</taxonomicName>
) (
<figureCitation id="4E9568F9E85DA57858EB549BFAD6A080" box="[1266,1336,475,501]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="11.[151,250,1834,1858]" captionTargetBox="[152,1436,1106,1811]" captionTargetId="figure-423@11.[151,1436,1101,1811]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURE 4. Host plant, two variations of Taquara micrantha. Taquara micrantha with pubescence on the abaxial surface as a host plant for Nhambikuara mima and Paryphthimoides brixius: 1a) leaves; 1b) close-up view of the node and abaxial part showing pubescence; 1c) inflorescence materials; 1d) host plant in situ. Taquara micrantha lacking pubescence for Splendeuptychia furina: 2a) leaves and inflorescence in situ; 2b) close-up view of nodes; 2c) close-up view of abaxial surface showing lack of pubescence; 2d) host plant in situ." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6420370" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6420370/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="51">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
: 2a–c. 6: 1e).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="D611747CE85DA5785CDE5763FD1AA3B8" blockId="14.[151,1437,259,717]" pageId="14" pageNumber="51">
See corresponding section of previous species for further detail. Based on 2021-FLP-IMM-0555, the egg was sampled from 
<taxonomicName id="11AE0FFFE85DA5785D225708FE25A314" box="[315,459,583,609]" class="Arachnida" family="Cryptogeobiidae" genus="Taquara" kingdom="Animalia" order="Opiliones" pageId="14" pageNumber="51" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="micrantha">
<emphasis id="E4DAA86EE85DA5785D225708FE25A314" box="[315,459,583,609]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="51">T. micrantha</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with variation of absence of pubescence in the abaxial part of the leaf. The individual associated with 
<taxonomicName id="11AE0FFFE85DA5785D50572CFE2AA3F0" baseAuthorityName="C. Felder &amp; R. Felder" baseAuthorityYear="1867" box="[329,452,619,645]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Magneuptychia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="51" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="harpyia">
<emphasis id="E4DAA86EE85DA5785D50572CFE2AA3F0" box="[329,452,619,645]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="51">M. harpyia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was located near a palm swamp, in a small forest area. At the date of collection the plant was 
<quantity id="1156D999E85DA5785CD057CFFEE7A3DF" box="[201,265,655,682]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.0" pageId="14" pageNumber="51" unit="m" value="0.4">0.4 m</quantity>
tall. The egg was found at a distance of 
<quantity id="1156D999E85DA5785ED257CFFCE5A3DF" box="[715,779,655,682]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="14" pageNumber="51" unit="m" value="0.1">0.1 m</quantity>
from the ground, on the abaxial surface, in the middle part of the leaf, between the midrib and margin of the leaf.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
